HEADWORD: Chilopoda
<hw>Chi*lop"o*da</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/ lip + <ets>-poda</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of
the orders of myriapods, including the centipedes. They have a single
pair of elongated legs attached laterally to each segment; well
developed jaws; and a pair of thoracic legs converted into poison fangs.
They are insectivorous, very active, and some species grow to the length
of a foot.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

